## Quick Start

1. Clone the repository
2. Install `arm-none-eabi-gcc` (≥ 10.x) and CMake (≥ 3.16)
3. Wire sensors and BLE module per the [pin table below](#hardware)
4. Configure and build:
   ```powershell
   cmake -S . -B build -DCMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE=toolchain-arm-none-eabi.cmake
   cmake --build build
   ```
5. Flash `build/tm4c123gxl.elf` via OpenOCD (see [Build, Flash & Debug](#build-flash--debug))
6. Open a serial terminal on **UART1 at 115200 baud**
7. Send `SYSTEM_STATUS` — all three sensors should be reported as OK

