## Project Highlights

- **Custom CMake build** — hand-configured toolchain file instead of IDE-generated project; keeps the build path explicit and auditable
- **CMSIS startup ownership** — custom `startup.c`, `system_TM4C123.c`, and `HardFault_Handler`; no vendor IDE scaffold
- **ISR-driven I2C driver** — interrupt-driven I2C2 with TM4C errata fix #I2C#07: `IntStatusEx()` read **before** `IntClearEx()` to avoid dropped events; mutex-protected with 20 ms ISR queue timeout
- **9-pulse GPIO bitbang bus recovery** — `recover_i2c_bus()` clocks out stuck SDA conditions before re-initializing the peripheral
- **FreeRTOS task architecture** — queues, stream buffers, software timers, and task notifications; no polling loops
- **Dual-rate sensor pipeline** — 1 s BLE send timer and 30 s EEPROM store timer driven independently via `xTaskNotify`
- **EEPROM circular ring buffer** — `eeprom_metadata_t` with `magic = 0xAB` boot guard; wraparound managed by `push_to_eeprom()`
- **Multi-task watchdog** — each task sets a dedicated liveness bit; `WDT_MANAGER_TASK` validates all bits and refreshes the hardware WDT; any hung task triggers `SysCtlReset()`
- **Sensor health monitor** — `check_sensor_health()` runs every 40 task loop ticks (~2 s); detects failures per sensor and calls the matching reinit + recalibration routine

