## Runtime Architecture

The firmware is organized around six FreeRTOS tasks:

| Task | Responsibility |
|------|---------------|
| `SENSOR_TASK` | Owns sensor reads, continuous sampling timers, EEPROM logging, sensor health monitoring |
| `BLE_RECEIVE_TASK` | Parses UART0 input into `sensor_modes_t` commands; pushes to `Ble_commands` queue |
| `BLE_SEND_TASK` | Dequeues `ble_msg` structs from `Ble_responses` and transmits over UART0 |
| `DEBUG_CONSOLE_TASK` | Parses UART1 text commands; pushes work to `debug_queue` |
| `DEBUG_TASK` | Executes diagnostics, I2C scan, direct sensor reads |
| `WDT_MANAGER_TASK` | Validates per-task liveness bits; refreshes hardware WDT0 |

### IPC Primitives

| Primitive | Usage |
|-----------|-------|
| `xStreamBuffer` | UART ISR → task data transfer (`uart_ble_rx_buffer`, `uart_debug_rx_buffer`) |
| `xQueue` | Command dispatch (`Ble_commands`, `Ble_responses`, `debug_queue`) and I2C ISR event queue |
| `xTaskNotify` | Timer callbacks → `SENSOR_TASK` for `NOTIFY_SEND` and `NOTIFY_STORE` |
| `xSemaphoreMutex` | UART print protection · I2C driver serialization |
| Software timers | `send_timer` (1 s auto-reload) · `store_timer` (30 s auto-reload) |

