## Build, Flash & Debug

### Prerequisites

- `arm-none-eabi-gcc` ≥ 10.x — [ARM Developer downloads](https://developer.arm.com/downloads/-/gnu-rm)
- CMake ≥ 3.16
- OpenOCD with TI ICDI support

### Build

```powershell
cmake -S . -B build -DCMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE=toolchain-arm-none-eabi.cmake
cmake --build build
```

Generated artifacts:

| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `build/tm4c123gxl.elf` | ELF with debug symbols |
| `build/tm4c123gxl.bin` | Raw binary for flashing |
| `build/tm4c123gxl.hex` | Intel HEX format |

### Flash via OpenOCD

```bash
openocd -f interface/ti-icdi.cfg -f board/ek-tm4c123gxl.cfg \
  -c "program build/tm4c123gxl.elf verify reset exit"
```

### Debug in VS Code

1. Install the **Cortex-Debug** extension
2. Install **OpenOCD**
3. Use the provided `.vscode/launch.json` (if included) or configure:
   - `interface/ti-icdi.cfg`
   - `board/ek-tm4c123gxl.cfg`
   - ELF path: `build/tm4c123gxl.elf`

