## Known Limitations

These are tracked issues being actively worked on:

- **`status &=` in I2C init** — chaining return codes with `&=` can silently swallow a failed transaction; replacing with per-call early-return error handling
- **`discrete_mode` flag not cleared** — after a one-shot command fires, the flag stays set and wastes one branch per 50 ms loop iteration; functionally harmless
- **BLE framing is plain newline-delimited text** — no checksum or sequence numbers; malformed packets are silently dropped
- **EEPROM validation is magic-byte only** — per-record CRC not yet implemented; a partial write leaves a corrupt record readable
- **Debug output is synchronous** — `UARTPrint()` calls in ISR-adjacent paths can cause brief blocking under heavy sensor load

---

## Roadmap

- Replace `status &=` error handling with early-return chains across all init paths
- Implement structured BLE framing with length prefix and checksum
- Add per-record CRC to EEPROM storage and validate on read
- Persist calibration data (MPU6050 bias, magnetometer hard-iron offsets) to EEPROM across power cycles
- Move debug printing fully off synchronous paths (DMA UART TX or dedicated print queue)
- Add `.vscode/launch.json` for one-click OpenOCD debug setup

